of customer service leaders report that poor internal data sharing between sales and support is a top driver of negative first-contact experiences, according to Forrester's 2025 B2B Customer Experience Index.

Stage 3: The First Support Interaction with Full Context
When the customer reaches out to support for the first time, whether via phone, chat, email, or self-service portal, the support agent should already know who they are, what they purchased, what they were promised, and whether there are any known risks or sensitivities associated with the account. This is not aspirational. It is achievable today with platforms that natively integrate CRM data into the contact center agent desktop.

CCaaS platforms such as Genesys Cloud, Five9, NICE CXone, and Salesforce Service Cloud Voice all offer native or deeply integrated CRM-to-agent-desktop experiences in 2026. When a customer call comes in, the platform matches the incoming phone number or email address to the CRM record, pulls the relevant data, and presents the agent with a screen pop that includes the customer's full profile before they have even said hello.

